29/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- An elderly Serb couple was attacked and stabbed repeatedly by unknown assailants in the village of Crkolez on Monday (28 March).
Nedeljko and Nevenka Vucic, 71 and 73, were rushed to hospital in Mitrovica for surgery.
Nevenka's condition was described as life-threatening.
In a statement Monday evening, the Serbian government in Belgrade condemned the attack on the couple and demanded that UNMIK better protect the Serb minority in Kosovo.
(Politika - 29/03/05;
AP, Reuters, Tanjug - 28/03/05)
